7</a><br />\n<br />\n<br />\nLong term 802.11ac has the headroom to support up to eight antennas each running at over 400Mbps each, but the fastest router to date only has four antennas. The reason is because antennas add cost and take up space and the smaller the device the less antennas they can fit so it becomes pointless adding more to a router. Typically:<br />\n<br />\n    Smartphones: 1 antenna<br />\n<br />\n    USB Adaptors: 1 or 2 antennas<br />\n<br />\n    Tablets: 2 antennas<br />\n<br />\n    Laptops: 2 antennas (occasionally 3 on desktop replacements)<br />\n<br />\n    Desktops: 3 or 4 antennas (PCI Express cards)"}]}